# Overview

This lab demonstrates how a reflected Cross-Site Scripting (XSS) vulnerability can still be exploited despite the presence of a Content Security Policy (CSP).

Although CSP is designed to prevent the execution of injected JavaScript, its effectiveness depends entirely on its configuration. In this lab, the application trusts an external script source that can be abused, allowing an attacker to bypass the CSP restrictions and execute arbitrary JavaScript in the victim's browser.

